main event: A bright white object, similar to a star, moved eastward across the sky in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania on September 9, 1965.
interesting points: The object was observed for 45 seconds during a 5-minute period., The observation was made by a civilian source., The motion was compared to that of a meteor or planet but differed in direction., There was no physical evidence or photographs associated with the sighting., The report includes findings from multiple observations around the same time with varying descriptions.
sighted object: a bright white object similar to a star
